Blood feeding reduviid bugs of the genera Triatoma, Rhodnius, and Panstrongylus. The most common vector in south America is Triatoma infestans. The vector lives up to 2 years.
Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever virus (CCHFV) is an enveloped, spherical virus with a tripartite, singlestranded, negative sense RNA genome, belonging to the genus Nairovirusin the family Bunyaviridae. It has 7 genotypes distinguished by the small (S) segment of the RNA.
